  channel_islands_data$sentence,

# Create a corpus with each data frame as a separate document
corpus <- Corpus(VectorSource(documents_list))

# Preprocess Text Data
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transformer(tolower))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(corpus, content_transformer(tolower)):
## transformation drops documents

corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeNumbers)

## documents

Transform corpus to a matrix

# Create Document-Term Matrix (DTM)
dtm <- DocumentTermMatrix(corpus)

# Convert DTM to a matrix
matrix <- as.matrix(dtm)

# Sum the word counts
word_counts <- colSums(matrix)

# Create a data frame for plotting
word_counts_df <- data.frame(word = names(word_counts), count = word_counts)

# Sort the data frame by count in descending order
word_counts_df <- word_counts_df[order(-word_counts_df$count),]

Visualize text

# Plot the bar plot using ggplot2 with the filtered data
ggplot(word_counts_df[1:21, ], aes(x = word, y = count)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "darkgreen") +
  geom_text(aes(label = count), vjust = -0.5, color = "black", size = 2.5) +  # Add count labels
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  ggtitle("Top 20 words in the text data (excluding stop words)") +
  xlab("Words") +
  ylab("Count")

# Build LDA Model
lda_model <- LDA(dtm,
                 k = 10,
                 control = list(seed = 321))  # Adjust 'k' based on the number of topics you want

eaop_topics <- tidy(lda_model, matrix = "beta")

eaop_top_terms <-
  eaop_topics %>%
  group_by(topic) %>%
  top_n(10, beta) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(topic, -beta)
# Define custom colors for each topic
topic_colors <- c("darkgoldenrod1",  "royalblue4",  "darkcyan", "lightcoral",  "burlywood4", "goldenrod3", "steelblue4", "lightcyan2", "lightpink2", "navajowhite3", "steelblue3", "goldenrod2", "lightcyan1", "thistle2", "antiquewhite3")

eaop_top_terms %>%
  mutate(term = reorder(term, beta)) %>%
  mutate(topic = paste("Topic #", topic)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(term, beta, fill = factor(topic))) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~ topic, scales = "free") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = topic_colors) +
  theme_minimal() +
    theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 18),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)  # Rotate x-axis labels
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Topic model of EAOP focus groups",
    caption = "Top terms by topic (betas)"
    ) +
  ylab("") +
  xlab("") +
         coord_flip()
